main event: An unidentified object was tracked visually for about 10 minutes on March 15, 1962.
interesting points: The object was described as round and pin-headed with a white color., The object's trajectory was straight but lost in haze on the horizon., Celestial navigation techniques were attempted but did not provide clear results., The sighting was made by highly reliable military personnel., No photographs were obtained during the observation.
witness description: LCDR USN, JTG USNR OOD, CMI LSN ASST NAV
